<div class="about-container"><div class="about-content"><div class="about-text"><h2>About Me</h2>

      <p class="about-intro">
        A researcher and academic with a background in economics, econometrics, and economic history. My expertise spans economic history, macroeconomics, climate economics, and international finance, with a particular passion for energy transition and geopolitics.
      </p>

      <h3>Current Position</h3>
      <p>
        I am a postdoctoral researcher at the <a href="https://www.pik-potsdam.de/en/home" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Potsdam Institute for Climate Impact Research (PIK)</a> in Germany, supervised by Franziska Piontek. My research examines the links between physical and financial risks of climate change using the REMIND economic model, focusing on climate damages and capital costs in developing nations.
      </p>

      <h3>Education</h3>
      <ul class="education-list">
        <li>
          <strong>PhD in Economics</strong> from <a href="https://uclouvain.be/en/index.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">UCLouvain Saint-Louis</a>
          <p>Focused on empirical assessments of financial interdependencies since the 1970s</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Master's degrees</strong> in Economics and Electrical Engineering from UCLouvain
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>University certificates</strong> in economic and social ethics, statistics, and radiation protection
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Career Highlights</h3>
      <ul class="career-list">
        <li>FNRS Research Fellowship recipient (2018-2022)</li>
        <li>Teaching experience in macroeconomics, econometrics, and statistics at UCLouvain</li>
        <li>Postdoctoral research at <a href="https://www.nccu.edu.tw/en" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">National Chengchi University (NCCU)</a> in Taiwan (2023-2024)</li>
        <li>Active international conference presenter</li>
      </ul>

